==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Olla-podrida
<hw>Ol`la-po*dri"da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.,
lit., a rotten pot. See <er>Olio</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
favorite Spanish dish, consisting of a mixture of several kinds of meat
chopped fine, and stewed with vegetables.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any incongruous mixture or miscellaneous collection;
an olio.</def> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>olm</ent>⟦br⟧
